\subsection*{Conceptual}
To develop a tool for easy and reliable prediction of concrete column prices to simplify estimating construction projects.

\subsection*{Logical}
Two models will be used:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item linear regression
    \item neural networks
\end{enumerate}

\vspace{0.4cm}
\noindent
The following data frames are intended:
\begin{table}[ht!]
    \caption{Intended data frames}
    \label{tab:intended_data_frames}

    \begin{center}
        \begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
            \hline
            \textbf{variable name} & \textbf{data frame} \\ \hline
             raw\_df & as read by pandas from the file \\ \hline
             df & cleaned \\ \hline
             rund & round columns \\ \hline
             eckig & angular columns \\ \hline
             oval & oval columns \\ \hline
             sbv & steel/concrete composite columns \\ \hline
             sb & reinforced concrete columns \\ \hline
             sbv\_rund & round steel/concrete composite columns \\ \hline
             sbv\_eckig & angular steel/concrete composite columns \\ \hline
             sbv\_oval & oval steel/concrete composite columns \\ \hline
             sb\_rund & round reinforced concrete columns \\ \hline
             sb\_eckig & reinforced concrete columns \\ \hline
             sb\_oval & reinforced concrete columns \\ \hline
        \end{tabular}
    \end{center}
\end{table}

It is planned to create the models for all the above data frames (expect raw\_df) to determine which data frames give the best results.\\
\clearpage
The following columns are considered for the analysis, as they should have the most significant impact on price. If the desired accuracy cannot be achieved, other columns/features should be considered.\\

\begin{table}[ht!]
    \caption{Considered columns/feature}
    \label{tab:considered_feature}

    \begin{center}
        \begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
            \hline
            \textbf{column/feature} & \textbf{ariable name} \\ \hline
             load & Nd \\ \hline
             cross section area & A \\ \hline
             column length & l \\ \hline
             volume & V \\ \hline
             unit price & Stückpreis \\ \hline
        \end{tabular}
    \end{center}
\end{table}

For the neural network, a normalization of the values is performed so that the magnitude of all values is in the same range (from 0 to 1)

\begin{table}[ht!]
    \caption{Normalization of columns/feature}
    \label{tab:normalization}
    \begin{center}
        \begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
            \hline
            \textbf{column/feature} & \textbf{adjustment} \\ \hline
             load & Nd/10000 \\ \hline
             cross section area & A x 10 \\ \hline
             column length & l/10 \\ \hline
             volume & V \\ \hline
             unit price & Stückpreis/10000 \\ \hline
        \end{tabular}
    \end{center}
\end{table}

\subsection*{Physical}
There are no high demands on the hardware; only the neural network training requires an apparent computational effort.
